msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.0"
msgid "76. Amūlakasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.76\">Monks’ Confession 76: the training rule on "
"groundlessly</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.76.1\""
">Bu-Pc.76.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.51\">BD.3.51</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1367</a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the "
"Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṃghādisesena "
"anuddhaṃsenti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six groundlessly accused a monk of "
"an offense entailing suspension.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.148
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.3"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1368</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.4"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṃghādisesena "
"anuddhaṃsessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six groundlessly accuse a monk of an "
"offense entailing suspension?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.6"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṃghādisesena "
"anuddhaṃsethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.148\">Vin.4.148</a> The Buddha rebuked "
"them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.9"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṃghādisesena "
"anuddhaṃsessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you groundlessly accuse a monk of an offense entailing "
"suspension?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.10"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.11"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:1.1.12"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṃghādisesena anuddhaṃseyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1369</a>‘If a monk groundlessly accuses another monk of an offense "
"entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.76.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.76.2.1\">Bu-Pc.76.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1370</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1371</a><term>Another monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>a different monk.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.8"
msgid "Amūlakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1372</a><term>Groundlessly</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.9"
msgid "adiṭṭhaṃ assutaṃ aparisaṅkitaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>not seen, not heard, not suspected.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.10"
msgid "Saṃghādisesenāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1373</a><term>An offense entailing suspension</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.11"
msgid "terasannaṃ aññatarena."
msgstr "<gloss>one of the thirteen.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.12"
msgid "Anuddhaṃseyyāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.52\">BD.3.52</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1374</a><term>Accuses</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.1.13"
msgid "codeti vā codāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he accuses him or causes him to be accused, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne upasampannasaññī amūlakena saṃghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.76.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.76.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1375</a>If it is one who is fully "
"ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he groundlessly "
"accuses him of an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne vematiko amūlakena saṃghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he "
"groundlessly accuses him of an offense entailing suspension, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī amūlakena saṃghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he groundlessly accuses him of an offense entailing "
"suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.4"
msgid "Ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā anuddhaṃseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1376</a>If he accuses someone of failure in conduct or "
"of failure in view, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampannaṃ anuddhaṃseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he accuses one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.76.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.76.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1377</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.3.2"
msgid "tathāsaññī codeti, vā codāpeti vā, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he accuses someone, or gets someone accused, according to what he has "
"perceived; if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc76:2.3.3"
msgid "Amūlakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1378</a>The sixth rule, the "
"training rule on groundlessly, is finished.</p>"
